BAAS marketplaces only have access to the DirectSales email notifications (Developer Portal > Settings > Customer Notifications).

They have a pre-set of email templates they can modify, but for some of them, the code that generates and sends the email only checks for the Non Direct Sales email template.

Example:
{code:java}
	@Override
	@Transactional(readOnly = true)
	public EmailNotification createSubscriptionSuspendedOverdueInvoiceNotification(String appName, Long invoiceId, int reminderDays) {
		Invoice invoice = invoiceDao.findById(invoiceId);
		String partner = invoice.getPartner();
		ChannelBean channel = channelManager.readChannel(partner);
		EmailTemplateParameters parameters = emailTemplateFactory.createSubscriptionSuspendedOverdueInvoiceParameters(channel, appName, invoice, reminderDays);
		return createEmailNotification(NotificationTemplateType.SUBSCRIPTION_SUSPENDED_OVERDUE_INVOICE, parameters, invoice.getUser().getLocale(), partner, false);
	}
{code}
It passes *false* for the DirectSales flag. It should instead check if its an invoice for Direct Sales :
{code:java}
boolean isDirectSales =  directSalesService.isDirectSales(invoice);
{code}

This must be fixed for the following email templates:
* SUBSCRIPTION_SUSPENDED_OVERDUE_INVOICE
* SUBSCRIPTION_SUSPENDED
* TICKET_SUPPORT_SUBSCRIPTION_CANCEL
* OFF_PURCHASE_ORDER
* ASYNCHRONOUS_PRODUCT_PURCHASE_NOTIFICATION

